sentences: Jonathan Mark Foreman (born October 22, 1976) is an American musician, the lead singer, guitarist, main songwriter and co-founder of the alternative rock band Switchfoot.
He started Switchfoot in 1996 with drummer Chad Butler and his brother Tim Foreman on bass guitar.

After several years, Foreman and his family moved back to Southern California, this time settling in San Diego.
Foreman married Emily Masen in 2002, and the couple had a daughter in 2012.

One of Foreman's favorite pastimes is surfing, and when not on tour, he resides in Cardiff-by-the-Sea, a small suburb of San Diego, California.
